headline: A Key Takeaway From Earnings Season: Signs of Consumer Weakness
summary: Earnings season is more than halfway over, and a clear laggard is emerging: companies that sell non-essential items to consumers.  A high ratio of companies—38%—have also missed consensus earnings forecasts.  The sector covers a broad swathe of the economy, encompassing a range of companies from Amazon and DoorDash to Tractor Supply and Marriott.

headline: Starbucks Revamps Rewards Tiers As App Activism And Rival Drinks Rise
summary: Starbucks (NasdaqGS:SBUX) is rolling out a major overhaul of its North American rewards program, returning to a three tier structure with more personalized perks. The refresh comes as union organizers urge customers to delete the Starbucks app and boycott digital ordering tied to rewards. At the same time, competitors such as Dutch Bros are introducing new drink offerings that directly target Starbucks core products. headline: A Look At Starbucks (SBUX) Valuation After Q1 Results And Turnaround Plan Updates
summary: Starbucks (SBUX) is back in focus after first quarter results showed revenue of US$9.9b and earnings per share of US$0.26, as CEO Brian Niccol’s Back to Starbucks plan gains early traction.
